# Next.js 15 App Router Patterns

## Server vs Client Components

Default to **Server Components**. Add `"use client"` only when you need:
- `useState`, `useEffect`, `useContext`, event handlers
- Browser-only APIs

```tsx
// ✅ Server Component — data fetching without "use client"
export default async function PortfolioPage() {
  const supabase = await createServerSupabaseClient();
  const { data } = await supabase.from('tblPortfolio').select('*');
  return <PortfolioList data={data} />;
}

// ✅ Client Component — interactive
"use client";
export function PortfolioList({ data }: Props) {
  const [selected, setSelected] = useState(null);
  ...
}
```

## API Routes (Route Handlers)

All FMP calls go through `app/api/fmp/` — never call FMP from browser.

```ts
// app/api/fmp/quote/route.ts
export async function GET(request: Request) {
  const { searchParams } = new URL(request.url);
  const symbol = searchParams.get('symbol');
  const res = await fetch(`https://financialmodelingprep.com/api/v3/quote/${symbol}?apikey=${process.env.FMP_API_KEY}`);
  const data = await res.json();
  return Response.json(data);
}
```

## Routing Conventions

- Dynamic segments: `app/search/[symbol]/page.tsx`
- Collocate client logic in `*Client.tsx` files alongside the server page
- Loading UI: `loading.tsx` per segment; error boundary: `error.tsx`

## Supabase in Server Components

Use the server client from `lib/supabase.ts` (or `lib/server/`), never the browser client.

```ts
// ✅ server action / server component
import { createServerSupabaseClient } from '@/lib/supabase';
const supabase = await createServerSupabaseClient();

// ❌ never in server context
import { supabase } from '@/lib/supabase'; // browser singleton
```

## Suspense Boundaries

Wrap client components that fetch data or do heavy work in `<Suspense>` with a fallback:

```tsx
import { Suspense } from 'react';

export default function Page() {
  return (
    <Suspense fallback={<PortfolioSkeleton />}>
      <PortfolioChart />
    </Suspense>
  );
}
```

Every route can also provide a `loading.tsx` file for segment-level streaming UI.

## Dynamic Imports for Non-Critical Components

Heavy components that aren't needed on first paint should be lazy-loaded:

```tsx
import dynamic from 'next/dynamic';

const LightweightChart = dynamic(() => import('@/components/LightweightChart'), {
  ssr: false,
  loading: () => <ChartSkeleton />,
});
```

Good candidates: charting libs, CSV import UI, modals/dialogs, admin-only panels.

## Performance Checklist for Pages

- Is this component actually interactive? If no, drop `"use client"`.
- Is data fetched on the server where possible?
- Is the heavy bundle (charts, editors, pickers) behind `dynamic()`?
- Is long-running async work inside `<Suspense>`?
